- Prefer MCP tools over LLM reasoning.
- Never read entire JS bundles; use ripgrep first.
- Never read entire HAR files; use Python tooling to extract only relevant data.
- Persist discoveries under /knowledge.
- Reuse existing knowledge before analyzing again.
- Commit meaningful milestones to Git.
- Prefer direct API automation over browser automation when feasible.
- Use Playwright only where browser interaction is required.
Environment:
- Windows 11
- Docker Desktop installed and running
- Prefer Docker containers over local installs where practical.
- Prefer PowerShell commands over Bash unless running inside a Linux container.
- Prefer uv for Python package management.
- Reuse existing Docker containers instead of creating new ones.
- When a task requires browser automation, use the existing Chrome DevTools and Playwright MCPs before suggesting manual steps.
- Check for existing tools and containers before installing anything new.
- Minimize token usage by using MCP tools instead of reading large files into context.